congVote.dailyDigestCategory1: Community Health And Medical Professionals Improve Our Nation Act of 2017
congVote.dailyDigestSummary: The House passed H.R. 3922, to extend funding for certain public health programs, by a yea-and-nay vote of 242 yeas to 174 nays, Roll No. 606.<P/>Rejected the Clyburn motion to recommit the bill to the Committee on Energy and Commerce with instructions to report the same back to the House forthwith with an amendment, by a yea-and-nay vote of 187 yeas to 231 nays, Roll No. 605.<P/>Pursuant to the Rule, the amendment printed in part A of H. Rept. 115-382, modified by the amendment printed in part B of H. Rept. 115-382, shall be considered as adopted, in lieu of the amendment in the nature of a substitute recommended by the Committee on Energy and Commerce now printed in the bill.

Rept. 115-382, modified by the amendment printed in part B of H. Rept. 115-382, shall be considered as adopted, in lieu of the amendment in the nature of a substitute recommended by the Committee on Energy and Commerce now printed in the bill.
